    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix null pointer dereference in free_fgmm_registration_accept function\n\n### Summary\nThere is a null pointer dereference due to missing NULL check before access downstream of function free_fgmm_registration_accept in openair3/NAS/NR_UE/5GS/5GMM/MSG/RegistrationAccept.c. The issue may be in free_fgmm_registration_accept or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\nThe problem occurs when the registration accept message contains a GUTI field that gets allocated but not properly freed, leading to potential memory corruption or crashes during NAS message processing.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/RegistrationAccept.c`: Added free_fgmm_registration_accept function with proper NULL checks\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/RegistrationAccept.h`: Added function declaration for free_fgmm_registration_accept\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg_sim.c`: Replaced manual memory freeing with proper free_fgmm_registration_accept call\n\n"
}